Which of the following commands will create a btrfs filesystem on the first SATA drive?
A)  mkfs /dev/sda1
B)  mkfs.btrfs /dev/sda
C)  mkfs.btr2fs /dev/sda1
D)  mkfs b /dev/sda
B
B. The mkfs.btrfs command is used to create btrfs filesystems on block storage anddoes not require the drive to be partitioned.
